sentences: Kwon Min-ah (born September 21, 1993), better known by the mononym Mina, is a South Korean singer and actress.
Mina has acted in television dramas, including Modern Farmer (2014) and All About My Mom (2015).

sentences: On August 6, 2020, Kwon posted a photograph on Instagram with the caption "Jinri-ya, I miss you", which was believed to be a reference to Sulli (Choi Jin-ri) of f(x), who committed suicide in 2019.
On August 6, 2020, Kwon posted a photograph on Instagram with the caption "Jinri-ya, I miss you", which was believed to be a reference to Sulli (Choi Jin-ri) of f(x), who committed suicide in 2019.

In a separate post, Kwon revealed that she had recently been hospitalized after a relapse in self harm, following a KakaoTalk conversation she had with an FNC Entertainment representative who believed Shin's apology to be sincere.
Two days later, in a since-deleted Instagram post, Kwon shared a graphic image of her slit wrist accompanied by an apparent suicide note stating:
The account wasn't even settled properly, the contract was 8 years, and there was no breakdown of expenditures for the illegal trainee debt of 3 billion won ($2,522,758.80 USD).
You don't even know how I was treated for 11 years, and to the bystanders or whatever, listen carefully.
At the end of October Kwon left the agency and went on a career hiatus to focus on her recovery.
